---
import { SITE_TITLE } from "../config";
---

<section id="intro" class="intro">
  <h1 class="name-gradient">Travis McGhee</h1>
  
  <p class="subhead">
    <span>Rutgers University Graduate | B.S. Information Technology and Informatics</span>
    <span>Minor in Digital Communication, Information, and Media</span>
  </p>

  <p class="focus-areas">Focus areas: IT security, privacy, networking, cloud, and data analytics.</p>
  
  <div class="roles">
    <span class="roles-label">Seeking:</span>
    <ul class="role-list">
      <li>SOC Analyst (Tier 1)</li>
      <li>Security Analyst (Entry-Level)</li>
      <li>IT Support (Entry-Level)</li>
      <li>Junior Cloud/Systems</li>
      <li>Threat Intelligence (Entry-Level)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>About</h2>
  <p>
    Hey, I'm Travis, a recent Rutgers grad who is into the investigative side of cybersecurity. I like digging into how systems break, how attackers think, and what logs can tell you when something feels off.
  </p>

  <p>
    Most of my coursework was around networking, security, data analytics, and privacy, which gave me a solid base to build on. I've worked on projects in Java and Python, built and managed databases, and used Tableau for data viz. Outside class, I run a Raspberry Pi with Pi-hole at home so I can tinker with DNS filtering and see what is actually moving across my network.
  </p>

  <h2>What I'm Looking For</h2>
  <p>
    I'm drawn to roles that involve threat detection, security event monitoring, and protecting systems from evolving threats. Whether analyzing logs, identifying suspicious activity, or contributing to incident response workflows, I want to join a team where I can apply what I've learned and keep growing in threat hunting, automation scripting, and cloud security. While cybersecurity is my primary focus, I'm also open to roles in system administration, cloud infrastructure, or IT operations where I can build a strong technical foundation.
  </p>

  <p>
    I rebuilt this site from WordPress to Astro and Netlify for speed and simplicity. If you're looking for someone curious, steady, and ready to learn fast, I'd love to connect.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .intro {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .name-gradient {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0ea5e9, #0284c7, #0369a1);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .subhead {
    color: rgb(var(--color-text-muted));
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .subhead span {
    display: block;
  }

  .focus-areas {
    color: rgb(var(--color-text-muted));
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .roles {
    color: rgb(var(--color-text-link));
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: rgb(var(--color-bg-code) / 0.3);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    border-left: 3px solid rgb(var(--color-text-link));
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .roles-label {
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .role-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .role-list li {
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgb(var(--color-bg-code) / 0.25);
    border: 1px solid rgb(var(--color-border-code) / 0.5);
  }

  h2 {
    color: rgb(var(--color-text-heading));
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }
</style>
